Congolese singer, songwriter and pianist Corneille Akilimali Bufole, popularly known as Cor Akim, has released a new song titled 'Yokela Ngai Mawa'. Akim, who is now based in Nairobi, sings in Lingala, Swahili, English and French with no boundaries, moving from rumba to zouk, Rnb to soul and many other music genres. Over the years, he has managed to present to fans an image of an artiste with a good musical background. Akim says in a statement that he is "determined to rock Africa and one of the artistes to look out for this 2020". Previously, he made headlines with songs like 'Mwasi', 'Kiuno Chako' and 'Sorry Really'.